        "title": "feat(ui): add collapsible toggle for recent sessions in sidebar",
        "body": "## Summary\r\n\r\n- Adds a collapse/expand toggle to the \"Recent\" sessions section in the web sidebar\r\n- Follows the exact same pattern as existing nav section groups (Chat, Control, Agent, Settings)\r\n- The entire \"Recent\" label row is a clickable button with a chevron icon that rotates -90deg when collapsed\r\n- Collapsed state persists to localStorage via `UiSettings.recentSessionsCollapsed`\r\n\r\n## Changes\r\n\r\n| File | Change |\r\n|------|--------|\r\n| `ui/src/ui/storage.ts` | Add `recentSessionsCollapsed` field and default value |\r\n| `ui/src/ui/app-render.ts` | Replace static label with collapsible button matching `.nav-section__label` pattern |\r\n| `ui/src/styles/layout.css` | Add styles matching `.nav-section__label`, `__label-text`, `__chevron` exactly |\r\n| `ui/src/i18n/locales/en.ts` | Add `nav.recentSessionsExpand` / `nav.recentSessionsCollapse` i18n keys |\r\n\r\n## Real behavior proof\r\n\r\nBehavior addressed: Sidebar recent sessions section now supports collapse/expand via a toggle button matching the nav section group pattern.\r\n\r\nReal environment tested: Local dev server (`pnpm ui:dev`) at http://localhost:5173/, macOS 26, Node 24, pnpm 11.2.2.\r\n\r\nExact steps or command run after this patch:\r\n1. Run `pnpm ui:dev` to start the Control UI dev server\r\n2. Open http://localhost:5173/ in a browser\r\n3. Observe the \"Recent\" label in the sidebar — it is now a clickable button with a chevron icon\r\n4. Click the \"Recent\" button → the session list collapses, chevron rotates clockwise to point right\r\n5. Click the \"Recent\" button again → the session list expands, chevron rotates back to point down\r\n6. Refresh the page → collapsed state is preserved from localStorage\r\n\r\nEvidence after fix:\r\n\r\nExpanded state (chevron down, 5 recent sessions visible, 237px width matching nav groups):\r\n![Expanded state](https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/3b7a79d4-4d14-4007-bdfc-fcc879b81be2)\r\n\r\nCollapsed state (chevron rotated right, list hidden, only label row visible):\r\n![Collapsed state](https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/045e6469-5121-406d-b38f-6701aea10c6b)\r\n\r\nAfter-fix proof — refresh persistence (video)\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/user-attachments/assets/d4059d46-552a-48ac-b68f-a19db9493fd6\r\n\r\n\r\nWidth verification via browser DevTools — `.sidebar-recent-sessions__label` computed width 237px, matching `.nav-section__label` exactly:\r\n```\r\nrecentLabelWidth: \"237px\"\r\nnavLabelWidth:    \"237px\"\r\nmatch:            true\r\n```\r\nType checks pass: `pnpm tsgo:core:test` and `pnpm tsgo:extensions:test` both green.\r\n\r\nObserved result after fix: Toggle works as expected — click collapses the list (display: none, chevron -90deg), click again expands it (display: grid, chevron 0deg). Width, font-size, padding, color, border-radius, and hover effects all match the adjacent nav section groups exactly. State persists across page refreshes.\r\n\r\nCloses #85510\r\n\r\n🤖 Generated with [Claude Code](https://claude.com/claude-code)",
